6. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES (5-STAGE ROADMAP)
---------------------------------------------------------
Phase 1: Foundation & Core MVP (Days/Weeks 1-3)
* Set up standard Android project structure with Kotlin and Jetpack Compose.
* Build the core Android Accessibility Service (`AccessibilityService`) to monitor permission dialogues.
* Implement a local SQLite Database using Room to store permission risks and translations (English/Hindi).
* Design minimal Consequence Cards UI with simple text (max 8 words) and local offline TTS support.

Phase 2: Security Hardening & Trust Seal (Days/Weeks 4-6)
* Upgrade SQLite to SQLCipher with AES-256 encryption.
* Implement boot-time database SHA-256/signature checks to block database tampering.
* Integrate Android's `filterTouchesWhenObscured` overlay security protection to prevent tapjacking.
* Deploy the custom Personal Trust Seal overlay and Google Play Integrity signature validations.

Phase 3: Vault, Stealth, & DPDP Compliance (Days/Weeks 7-9)
* Develop the Duress-Aware Private Vault utilizing Room (encrypted partition) with Biometric/PIN prompts.
* Create the Panic Wipe trigger (wiping all logs and vault keys from keystore).
* Design the Stealth Mode configurations (launcher-hiding routines).
* Build the local DPDP-compliant Audit Trail and generate ZKCP (Zero-Knowledge Consent Proof) signature bundles locally.

Phase 4: ML & Computer Vision Protection (Days/Weeks 10-13)
* Integrate TensorFlow Lite (TFLite) or ONNX Runtime Mobile inside the background service.
* Implement screenshot analysis for spoofed popup UI templates (phishing overlay defense).
* Set up the on-device Behavioral Pattern Engine (FSM) tracking session-level permission velocity/escalation alerts.

Phase 5: Chrome Companion & Testing (Days/Weeks 14-16)
* Build the Chrome extension companion (MV3) with side-panel API and document_start injection.
* Connect local settings sync if relevant, or set up enterprise school/NGO deployments.
* Conduct extensive security auditing (MobSF static scan, Semgrep check) and user testing.

