7. PHASE 1 COMPLETED IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS & RISKS RESEARCH
---------------------------------------------------------
- File Structure Created:
  * `settings.gradle.kts` & `build.gradle.kts` (Project root)
  * `gradle/libs.versions.toml` (Dependency catalog)
  * `app/build.gradle.kts` (Compose, Room, Kapt dependencies)
  * `app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml` (Registers Accessibility Service & Dashboard MainActivity)
  * `app/src/main/res/xml/accessibility_service_config.xml` (Flags windowStateChanged + canRetrieveWindowContent)
  * `app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml` & `themes.xml` (Metadata resources & Light theme base)
  * `app/src/main/res/drawable/` (Adaptive launcher assets)
  * `app/src/main/java/com/mpowernet/shesafe/SheSafeApplication.kt` (Room database initialization)
  * `app/src/main/java/com/mpowernet/shesafe/data/` (Room Entities: `PermissionRule`, `ConsentLog` & corresponding DAOs and AppDatabase with pre-seeded data)
  * `app/src/main/java/com/mpowernet/shesafe/accessibility/` (Core `PermissionInterceptorService` and `LifecycleRegistryHelper` for Compose overlays)
  * `app/src/main/java/com/mpowernet/shesafe/MainActivity.kt` (Dashboard displaying state, toggle settings, and local logs)

- Key Architecture & Security Choices:
  * Window Overlay Type: Used `TYPE_ACCESSIBILITY_OVERLAY` for the visual card. This bypasses the need for the dangerous `SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW` permission (draw-over-other-apps) which is confusing and difficult for first-time users to enable.
  * Compose inside WindowManager: Handled lifecycle tree registration inside the AccessibilityService context using custom `LifecycleOwner` and `SavedStateRegistry` mocks, enabling native, interactive Compose views on top of system dialogs.
  * Offline-First Rules seeding: Created database callback to seed rules during database instantiation, ensuring zero-cloud translation rules are ready instantly.

- Research on Technical Interception Risks:
  * Node Tree Latency: Android does not populate accessibility node trees immediately upon window changes. We introduced a 250ms coroutine delay to allow the layout tree to settle before scanning nodes.
  * System Package Variations: Permission dialog package names vary across vendors (e.g. `com.google.android.permissioncontroller` vs `com.android.packageinstaller`). Handled by scanning for substring matches on both keywords.
  * Window Touch Leakage: Configured overlay layout flags to include split-touch/outside touch handling to protect the overlay window from being bypassed or allowing click-through redirection.

